HEADWORD: Rchauff
<hw>R⟦eacute⟧`chauf`f⟦eacute⟧"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[F., orig. p.p. of <ets>r⟦eacute⟧chauffer</ets> 8warm over. See
<er>Chafe</er>, <pos>v. t.</pos>]</ety> <def>A dish of food that has
been warmed again, hence, fig., something made up from old material; a
rehash.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><q>It is merely a <qex>r⟦eacute⟧chauff⟦eacute⟧</qex> of ancient
philosophies.</q> <rj><qau>F. W. H. Myers.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Recheat</ent>⟦br⟧
